The paper discusses the emergence and evolution of complex networks from simple behaviours, which is a topic that falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of paracrine chemotaxis behaviours also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and self-organizing systems (cs.SI). The study of network resilience and adaptation to changing environmental conditions is also relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
